01:04:24,485 --> 01:04:27,822
I keep wondering if it's right for Mom

798
01:04:28,364 --> 01:04:30,283
to stay bedridden there
until her final moments.

799
01:04:32,952 --> 01:04:34,036
All right.

800
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:37,540
Then I'll tell the realtor
that we're selling this store space.

801
01:04:39,959 --> 01:04:41,168
You want to come with us?

802
01:04:41,627 --> 01:04:43,045
Of course.

803
01:04:44,088 --> 01:04:46,215
Why don't you want me to come?

804
01:04:47,592 --> 01:04:49,093
Where will I live, then?

805
01:04:50,261 --> 01:04:51,554
Will you be okay though?

806
01:04:52,346 --> 01:04:54,307
-You don't have to...
-Gosh, seriously.

807
01:04:54,599 --> 01:04:56,601
Are you going to keep trying
to separate me from you two?

808
01:04:57,310 --> 01:04:59,270
I told you that I'm scared to sleep alone.

809
01:05:12,992 --> 01:05:15,578
You can have it.
I don't like chicken wings.

810
01:05:19,457 --> 01:05:21,250
Is it Min-su that likes chicken wings?

811
01:05:22,168 --> 01:05:25,129
What's gotten into you?
I'm surprised you remember that.

812
01:05:26,339 --> 01:05:27,506
I remember, of course.

813
01:05:29,258 --> 01:05:31,344
Next time when Min-su comes over,

814
01:05:31,552 --> 01:05:34,180
you two should go for some beer
and fried chicken.

815
01:05:37,058 --> 01:05:38,225
Yes, we should.

816
01:05:42,897 --> 01:05:48,152
REALTOR'S OFFICE

817
01:05:50,905 --> 01:05:53,491
REALTOR'S OFFICE

818
01:05:53,574 --> 01:05:56,911
HYOJA TRAIL, HYOJA NURSING
HOSPITAL, MINERAL SPRING

819
01:06:07,755 --> 01:06:11,550
HYOJA NURSING HOSPITAL

820
01:06:20,393 --> 01:06:21,936
Hello.

821
01:06:25,356 --> 01:06:26,440
Hello.

822
01:06:37,618 --> 01:06:39,161
It's a beautiful day, isn't it?

823
01:06:40,746 --> 01:06:41,831
It is indeed.

824
01:06:43,833 --> 01:06:46,252
It's a dazzlingly beautiful day.

825
01:06:52,174 --> 01:06:54,301
When did you move here?

826
01:06:59,056 --> 01:07:00,182
Me?

827
01:07:02,393 --> 01:07:04,061
How long ago was it?

828
01:07:07,231 --> 01:07:08,774
What about you? When did you move here?

829
01:07:10,818 --> 01:07:12,236
Me? I...

830
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:22,663
Actually, when did I move here?

831
01:07:26,167 --> 01:07:28,794
You don't have to force yourself
to recall what you don't remember.

832
01:07:30,880 --> 01:07:31,964
Just...

833
01:07:33,340 --> 01:07:35,176
remember the moments...

834
01:07:36,844 --> 01:07:37,928
when you were happy.

835
01:07:39,346 --> 01:07:41,724
Happy moments.

836
01:07:47,313 --> 01:07:49,023
Ma'am, when was...

837
01:07:50,316 --> 01:07:52,193
the happiest moment in your life so far?

838
01:08:00,826 --> 01:08:03,204
I wouldn't say it was any special day.

839
01:08:05,122 --> 01:08:06,290
You see,

840
01:08:09,210 --> 01:08:11,879
those ordinary days made me happy.

841
01:08:13,839 --> 01:08:15,299
Around the time when the whole village

842
01:08:15,382 --> 01:08:18,052
was filled with the aroma of rice
being cooked,

843
01:08:19,845 --> 01:08:22,848
I'd start cooking rice
on the stove as well.

844
01:08:24,517 --> 01:08:28,729
My son had just started walking

845
01:08:30,022 --> 01:08:31,232
back then.

846
01:08:33,317 --> 01:08:35,027
I'd hold his hand...

847
01:08:36,195 --> 01:08:38,072
and go out to the front yard with him.

848
01:08:40,074 --> 01:08:43,786
Then we'd see the sun setting...

849
01:08:46,330 --> 01:08:47,998
from afar.

850
01:08:49,500 --> 01:08:51,502
Where's your daddy?

851
01:08:51,585 --> 01:08:53,212
Let's go see whereabouts he is.

852
01:08:59,844 --> 01:09:01,804
Dae-sang, who's that?

853
01:09:01,887 --> 01:09:03,931
Who's that? Who is he?

854
01:09:08,519 --> 01:09:09,812
Come here, my pumpkin.

855
01:09:18,863 --> 01:09:19,947
What a beautiful sunset.

856
01:09:21,407 --> 01:09:22,783
I know, right?

857
01:09:23,325 --> 01:09:24,785
I can never get sick of this view.

858
01:09:25,077 --> 01:09:28,164
I think sunsets are more beautiful
than flowers.

859
01:09:28,873 --> 01:09:30,040
I agree.

860
01:09:44,722 --> 01:09:48,934
Those were the happiest moments.

861
01:09:51,478 --> 01:09:52,980
Those days.

862
01:09:57,026 --> 01:09:59,987
My mother is suffering from
Alzheimer's disease.

863
01:10:01,780 --> 01:10:03,282
But perhaps,

864
01:10:05,367 --> 01:10:07,953
she's simply reliving

865
01:10:09,371 --> 01:10:11,415
the happiest moments of her life.

866
01:12:21,879 --> 01:12:23,839
Now, stay with me here.

867
01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:27,176
Don't go anywhere.

868
01:12:28,677 --> 01:12:32,431
My life was blighted
by misfortune at times,

869
01:12:33,724 --> 01:12:35,851
but there were also happy moments.

870
01:12:37,353 --> 01:12:41,106
They say that life is nothing
but a mere dream,

871
01:12:41,732 --> 01:12:44,818
but I was still grateful for my life.

872
01:12:46,862 --> 01:12:50,324
The cold, brisk air at dawn,

873
01:12:50,949 --> 01:12:54,203
the sweet breeze
right before flowers start to bloom,

874
01:12:54,995 --> 01:12:58,791
and the scent of sunset
that fills the air at sundown.

875
01:13:00,084 --> 01:13:03,754
Every single day was dazzlingly beautiful.

876
01:13:04,922 --> 01:13:08,008
Even if you're struggling right now,

877
01:13:09,426 --> 01:13:11,887
everyone alive

878
01:13:12,179 --> 01:13:16,934
has the right to enjoy all this every day.

879
01:13:18,352 --> 01:13:21,063
Even if one ordinary day is followed

880
01:13:21,230 --> 01:13:24,191
by another ordinary day,

881
01:13:25,150 --> 01:13:28,904
life is still worth living.

882
01:13:30,989 --> 01:13:33,200
Don't waste the present

883
01:13:33,492 --> 01:13:35,953
regretting the past

884
01:13:36,161 --> 01:13:39,123
and worrying about the future.

885
01:13:40,207 --> 01:13:42,084
Live this day

886
01:13:42,876 --> 01:13:44,336
beautifully.

887
01:13:45,087 --> 01:13:48,882
You deserve it.

888
01:13:50,134 --> 01:13:52,386
To all of you who were a mom,

889
01:13:52,928 --> 01:13:54,388
a sister,

890
01:13:55,139 --> 01:13:58,142
a daughter,

891
01:13:59,184 --> 01:14:00,936
and

892
01:14:01,687 --> 01:14:03,230
yourself.

893
01:14:06,066 --> 01:14:10,571
THANK YOU FOR WATCHING
THE LIGHT IN YOUR EYES

894
01:14:12,489 --> 01:14:14,533
SPECIAL THANKS TO SON SOOK

895
